It is my greatest honor to get to celebrate love all over the world. To every one of you who have listened to this little song throughout the years that my mom wrote for me as a Valentine in 1994 and my dad produced, I say an honest, humble thank you. The everlasting power of love, and the kindness that you share in your comments means so much to my parents, and to me. These comments continue to brighten our days, and remind us that there is so much good in this world. Perspective is everything. I hope you enjoy this new duet with little Amy, and that this song keeps your own inner child full of love, and singing for years to come. ❤️ Happy Holidays to you and yours. My parents and I send you lots of love, good health, and happiness! 🤗

I'm at a place now with my personal health where exercise is built in to my lifestyle, and food choices support my optimal wellbeing. None of it feels like a chore. I'm working with myself instead of against.

My emotions factored into this way more than I realized. I replaced unhealthy coping mechanisms with awareness. I now write to process my emotions, instead of storing those emotions in my body.

It has taken years to get to this point, and knowing now that my physical, mental, spiritual and emotional health are all in alignment...it's the best gift I have ever given myself.

Before you can help others, you've first got to help yourself. ❤️

It’s time I start sharing more of the healthy recipes I’m whipping up in my kitchen! This can be made in under 30 minutes, and is completely worth your effort. Here’s last night’s dinner:

I preheated my pan over medium high heat for at least 10 minutes. While it’s heating, I open up 1 package of @eelriverorganicbeef 85/15 ground beef, and section into 4 patties. I use a stainless steel burger press ($20 bucks on Amazon) to create uniform burgers of the same thickness. Season both sides of the patties with Himalayan salt and pepper. When the pan is hot enough (water should bead in the pan) place all four patties in your pan, cook for 5 minutes, then flip and cook for another 5. Once cooked on both sides, remove burgers from pan, and let rest for at least 3 minutes. 

For the salsa, cut up 1 red bell pepper, 1 small red onion, and 1 mango. Add that all to a bowl, toss with juice from 1 lime, Himalayan salt, and a generous shake of cayenne pepper. 

Once your burgers are cooked and the salsa is ready, it’s easy assembly. Place a handful of arugula in a bowl, drizzle on extra virgin olive oil, add grated Parmesan cheese, top with one of the burger patties, and spoon on a generous amount of the salsa. 

Congratulations, you’ve now got yourself a fresh, flavorful protein packed feast. Enjoy! ✅😋

Oh hi! It’s me, former perfectionist Amy Castle here. This is now the FOURTH consistent weekend of my posting covers. If you’ve been watching my videos for a long time, you know that consistent uploads…had not been one of my strengths. Well, that’s been changing recently. Yay for accepting yourself as you are! I decided that showing up is better than only doing so if the outcome is exactly how I envision it. I’ve been playing guitar now for 22 months, and really enjoy working on these cover songs. I picked this cover, because the lyrics resonate deeply. It’s has been one of those songs that I can listen to over and over again. The story told is one a lot of us relate to. Aren’t those the most powerful songs? #acousticcovers #sheusedtobemine

Thankful for every day that I get to wake up, learn more, and help others. 🙏🏻❤️ Lately I’ve been a voracious reader, devoting time nearly every day to read about others’ life experiences that interest me. It feels really good to give my eyes a break from staring at screens so much, and sit with paper books, letting my mind fully get into the content. I’ve been thinking about it as strengthening my attention span, slowly upping how long I sit at a time and read. I’ve been aiming for about an hour at a time, and if I’m able to hook my attention for longer, even better. I think our attention is the most valuable currency, so I’ve been mindful as to where I’m investing mine. Here’s to strengthening your attention span! 💪🏻🧠

Over the years, my eating habits have changed a lot. I used to be a big snacker, eating a lot of pre-packaged foods. Post 2020, I’ve found myself cooking much more at home, paying closer attention to the system I utilize to prepare food. Nowadays it’s a lot of grass fed ground beef, eggs, fruit, and dairy (fermented and raw when possible,) with honey and maple syrup in moderation. I also LOVE cabbage. Making lots of soups. Onions, garlic, and ginger get added in frequently. Roasting various squashes is also a favorite pastime of mine. Tomato paste is my BFF. Celtic salt on everything. The biggest dynamic that has changed for me is my relationship to the foods I’m eating, and the mindset I’m in while I eat. Food is nourishment, food is a joy, the foods I choose to eat best support my body’s wellbeing. What foods make you feel the best? Let me know in a comment below.
